# Angular 21 Best Practices

## Architecture

- **Standalone components only** — NgModules are legacy; never use for new code
- **Zoneless by default** — Zone.js is removed; signals drive change detection
- **Signals are the primary mental model** — not optional; tooling and DevTools assume them
- Feature-based folder structure with standalone routes
- Smart (container) components handle data; dumb (presentational) components render via `input()`/`output()`
- Keep components thin — delegate business logic to services
- One service per domain concern (`StockPriceService`, `PortfolioService`)

```
src/app/
  features/
    stocks/
      components/
      services/
      models/
      stocks.routes.ts
    portfolio/
      ...
  core/            # singleton services, guards, interceptors
  shared/          # reusable components, pipes, directives
```

## Components

### Signals (Default Mental Model)

All signal APIs are stable: `signal()`, `computed()`, `effect()`, `linkedSignal()`, `toSignal()`.

- Use **signals** for all component state — `BehaviorSubject` for UI state is a code smell
- Use `input()`, `output()`, `model()` function APIs — **never** `@Input()`/`@Output()` decorators
- Use `computed()` for derived values — never store what you can compute
- Use `linkedSignal()` for writable signals that reset when a source changes

```typescript
@Component({ ... })
export class StockCardComponent {
  stock = input.required<Stock>();
  priceChange = computed(() => this.stock().currentPrice - this.stock().openPrice);
  select = output<string>();
}
```

### linkedSignal

Writable signal that auto-resets when a source signal changes — replaces manual `effect()` + `set()` patterns:

```typescript
selectedSymbol = input.required<string>();
quantity = linkedSignal({
  source: this.selectedSymbol,
  computation: () => 1,
});
```

### model() — Two-Way Binding

`model()` replaces the `@Input() + @Output()` two-way binding pattern:

```typescript
// Child component
checked = model.required<boolean>();

toggle() {
  this.checked.set(!this.checked());
}

// Parent template
<app-toggle [(checked)]="isActive" />
```

### Signal Queries

Use function-based queries — **never** `@ViewChild()`/`@ContentChild()` decorators:

```typescript
chart = viewChild.required<StockChartComponent>('chart');
items = viewChildren(StockRowComponent);

resetChart() {
  this.chart().reset();
}
```

### Change Detection — Zoneless by Default

Angular 21 removed Zone.js from the default bootstrap. New projects are zoneless out of the box:

```typescript
bootstrapApplication(AppComponent, {
  providers: [
    provideZonelessChangeDetection(),
    // ...
  ]
});
```

- Components re-render only when: signals change, template events fire, or `markForCheck()` is called
- No global async patching — ~33KB bundle reduction, 30-40% rendering improvement
- `OnPush` is the standard (aliased as `ChangeDetectionStrategy.Eager` for `Default`)
- Avoid mutating objects/arrays — always create new references
- Replace any `NgZone` usage with `afterNextRender()` / `afterEveryRender()`

### Templates

- Use `@if`, `@for`, `@switch` built-in control flow — **never** `*ngIf`, `*ngFor`, `*ngSwitch`
- `track` is mandatory in `@for` to avoid DOM thrashing
- `@defer` for lazy-loading heavy components
- `@switch` supports exhaustive checks (Angular 21.2)
- `instanceof` operator supported in templates (Angular 21.2)
- Arrow functions supported in template expressions (Angular 21.2)
- Keep templates lean — move logic to `computed()` or pipes

```html
@for (stock of stocks(); track stock.symbol) {
  <app-stock-card [stock]="stock" (select)="onSelect($event)" />
}

@defer (on viewport) {
  <app-stock-chart [data]="chartData()" />
} @placeholder {
  <div class="chart-skeleton"></div>
}
```

### Component Communication

| Direction | Method |
|---|---|
| Parent → Child | `input()` / `input.required()` |
| Child → Parent | `output()` |
| Two-way binding | `model()` with `[( )]` syntax |
| Siblings | Shared service with signals |
| Deep nesting | Service at appropriate injector level, or signal store |

## Services & Dependency Injection

- Use `inject()` function — **not** constructor injection
- Services are `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })` for singletons
- Scope services at feature level when they shouldn't be global
- Services own business logic and data access — components orchestrate UI

## Resource API

Use `resource()` / `rxResource()` / `httpResource()` for reactive async data loading — replaces manual `subscribe` + loading/error state management. Compose resources via `ResourceSnapshot` for dependent queries.

```typescript
@Component({ ... })
export class StockDetailComponent {
  symbol = input.required<string>();

  stockPrice = httpResource<StockPrice>(() => ({
    url: `/api/stocks/${this.symbol()}/price`,
  }));

  // Access: stockPrice.value(), stockPrice.status(), stockPrice.error()
}
```

For RxJS-based streams (`params`/`stream` API):

```typescript
priceHistory = rxResource<PriceHistory[], string>({
  params: () => this.symbol(),
  stream: ({ params, abortSignal }) =>
    this.http.get<PriceHistory[]>(`/api/stocks/${params}/history`, { signal: abortSignal }),
});
```

Resource status: `'idle' | 'loading' | 'reloading' | 'resolved' | 'error'`

## Signal Forms (Experimental)

Angular 21 introduces experimental Signal Forms — a signal-native replacement for Reactive Forms. Use for **non-production** or **new greenfield** forms where you accept API instability.

```typescript
import { form, FormField, required, email } from '@angular/forms/signals';

loginModel = signal<LoginData>({ email: '', password: '' });

loginForm = form(this.loginModel, (fieldPath) => {
  required(fieldPath.email, { message: 'Email is required' });
  email(fieldPath.email, { message: 'Enter a valid email' });
  required(fieldPath.password, { message: 'Password is required' });
});
```

```html
<input [formField]="loginForm.controls.email" />
```

- Define a signal model, wrap with `form()`, bind with `[formField]`
- Schema-based validation as second argument to `form()`
- No `ControlValueAccessor` needed for custom controls
- **For production forms, continue using typed Reactive Forms** until Signal Forms stabilizes

## RxJS

- Reserve RxJS for **async streams**: WebSocket, real-time event coordination, complex orchestration
- For HTTP, prefer `httpResource()` / `rxResource()` over manual RxJS
- When using observables, prefer `toSignal()` over manual `.subscribe()` or `async` pipe
- If you must subscribe, unsubscribe via `takeUntilDestroyed()` or `DestroyRef`
- Avoid nested subscribes — use `switchMap`, `mergeMap`, `concatMap`, `exhaustMap`
- Use `shareReplay({ bufferSize: 1, refCount: true })` for multicasted streams

```typescript
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class StockStreamService {
  connectToLivePrices(symbols: string[]): Observable<PriceUpdate> {
    return webSocket<PriceUpdate>(`wss://api.example.com/prices`).pipe(
      filter(update => symbols.includes(update.symbol)),
      retry({ count: 3, delay: 1000 }),
      shareReplay({ bufferSize: 1, refCount: true })
    );
  }
}
```

## State Management

| Complexity | Tool |
|---|---|
| Component-local | `signal()`, `computed()`, `linkedSignal()` |
| Async data | `httpResource()`, `rxResource()`, `resource()` |
| Shared feature state | Service with signals |
| Complex global state | NgRx SignalStore |

### NgRx SignalStore

```typescript
export const StockStore = signalStore(
  withState<StockState>({ stocks: [], loading: false, error: null }),
  withComputed(({ stocks }) => ({
    activeStocks: computed(() => stocks().filter(s => s.status === 'active')),
  })),
  withMethods((store, stockService = inject(StockPriceService)) => ({
    loadStocks: rxMethod<void>(
      pipe(
        tap(() => patchState(store, { loading: true })),
        switchMap(() => stockService.getAll()),
        tap(stocks => patchState(store, { stocks, loading: false }))
      )
    ),
  }))
);
```

## Routing

- Lazy load feature routes for smaller initial bundle
- Use functional guards and resolvers
- Preload visible routes (`PreloadAllModules` or custom strategy)

```typescript
export const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: 'stocks',
    loadChildren: () => import('./features/stocks/stocks.routes').then(m => m.STOCK_ROUTES),
    canActivate: [authGuard],
  },
];
```

## Forms (Production)

- **Typed Reactive Forms** (`FormGroup<T>`) for complex validation, dynamic fields, cross-field logic
- **Template-driven** only for trivial cases (search bar)
- Custom validators as pure functions; async validators for server-side checks
- Signal Forms (experimental) for greenfield exploration only

## HTTP & Interceptors

- For simple requests, prefer `httpResource()` — automatic loading/error/caching
- For complex flows, centralize API calls in services with `HttpClient`
- Use functional interceptors for auth tokens, error handling, logging
- Use `withFetch()` in `provideHttpClient()` for modern fetch-based transport

```typescript
export const authInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) => {
  const token = inject(AuthService).getToken();
  const authReq = token
    ? req.clone({ setHeaders: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } })
    : req;
  return next(authReq);
};
```

## Angular Aria (Developer Preview)

- Headless, accessible-first components you can fully style
- Use for custom UI where Angular Material is too opinionated
- Built with accessibility as a priority — ARIA attributes handled automatically

## Testing

- Unit test services with `TestBed` or plain instantiation
- Component tests with `ComponentFixture` — test inputs, outputs, and DOM behavior
- Use `provideHttpClientTesting()` for HTTP tests (not `HttpClientTestingModule`)
- Use `fakeAsync` + `tick` for time-dependent tests
- Prefer `harness` from Angular CDK for testing Material components
- **Vitest** supported as unit-test runner (Angular 21.2) alongside Karma/Jest
- E2E with Playwright or Cypress for critical user journeys

## Performance

- Zoneless change detection — default and most performant (~33KB less, 30-40% faster renders)
- Lazy load routes and heavy components with `@defer`
- `@defer (on viewport)` for below-the-fold content
- `track` expression in every `@for` block
- Avoid expensive work in templates — use `computed()` or pipes
- Bundle analysis with `source-map-explorer`
- Use Web Workers for CPU-heavy computation (e.g., real-time chart calculations)
- Nested animations support (Angular 21.2)

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML first (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<label>`)
- Consider **Angular Aria** headless components for custom accessible UI
- `aria-*` attributes only when native semantics aren't enough
- Keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Use Angular CDK `a11y` module (focus trap, live announcer)
- Lint with `angular-eslint` and test with screen reader

## TypeScript

- **TypeScript 6** supported (Angular 21.2)
- `strict: true` — never relax it
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` + type guards
- Discriminated unions for multi-shape state
- Use `instanceof` in templates for type narrowing (Angular 21.2)
